# Backend Database Patterns

Prisma 5 ORM. Aurora PostgreSQL 16. Her query intentional — premature optimization yok, ama N+1 kabul edilmez.

## Prisma Client Injection

Service'ler `PrismaService` kullanır:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class UsersService {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  async findById(id: string) {
    return this.prisma.users.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }
}
```

`PrismaService` connection lifecycle'ı yönetir (NestJS lifecycle hooks).

## Transaction Pattern

Multi-table write = transaction zorunlu:

```typescript
async create(input, actor) {
  return this.prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    const user = await tx.users.create({ data: ... });
    await tx.user_roles.create({ data: { user_id: user.id, role_id: ... } });
    await tx.audit_logs.create({ data: ... });
    return user;
  });
}
```

Transaction içinde:
- Exception → otomatik rollback
- `tx` kullan (not `this.prisma`) — aynı connection'da izolasyon
- Side effect (notifications, emails) transaction DIŞINDA — commit sonrası EventEmitter

Isolation level default `READ_COMMITTED`. Concurrency-sensitive query'lerde `SERIALIZABLE`:

```typescript
await this.prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  // ...
}, { isolationLevel: Prisma.TransactionIsolationLevel.Serializable });
```

## Encryption Middleware

PII kolon'ları Prisma middleware ile otomatik encrypt/decrypt:

```typescript
// apps/api/src/common/encryption/encryption.middleware.ts
export function createEncryptionMiddleware(encryption: EncryptionService) {
  return async (params: Prisma.MiddlewareParams, next) => {
    // On write: encrypt
    if (params.action === 'create' || params.action === 'update') {
      if (params.model === 'users') {
        if (params.args.data.email) {
          params.args.data.email = encryption.deterministicEncrypt(
            params.args.data.email.toLowerCase()
          );
        }
        if (params.args.data.phone) {
          params.args.data.phone = encryption.probabilisticEncrypt(params.args.data.phone);
        }
      }
    }

    // On where clause: encrypt lookup fields
    if (params.action === 'findUnique' || params.action === 'findFirst' || 
        params.action === 'findMany' || params.action === 'update') {
      if (params.model === 'users' && params.args.where?.email) {
        params.args.where.email = encryption.deterministicEncrypt(
          params.args.where.email.toLowerCase()
        );
      }
    }

    const result = await next(params);

    // On read: decrypt
    if (params.model === 'users' && result) {
      const rows = Array.isArray(result) ? result : [result];
      for (const row of rows) {
        if (row.email) row.email = encryption.deterministicDecrypt(row.email);
        if (row.phone) row.phone = encryption.probabilisticDecrypt(row.phone);
      }
    }

    return result;
  };
}
```

Middleware `PrismaService.onModuleInit()`'te register:

```typescript
onModuleInit() {
  this.$use(createEncryptionMiddleware(this.encryption));
}
```

## Query Optimization

### Avoid N+1

```typescript
// ✗ N+1
const users = await this.prisma.users.findMany();
for (const user of users) {
  user.roles = await this.prisma.user_roles.findMany({ where: { user_id: user.id } });
}

// ✓ Single query with include
const users = await this.prisma.users.findMany({
  include: { roles: true },
});
```

### Select vs Include

`select` daha küçük payload:

```typescript
// If you only need specific fields
await this.prisma.users.findMany({
  select: { id: true, first_name: true, last_name: true },
});

// If you need relations:
await this.prisma.users.findMany({
  include: { roles: true, company: true },
});
```

Network + memory büyük data set'ler için `select` tercih.

### Cursor-Based Pagination

Büyük tablolarda offset yavaş — cursor kullan:

```typescript
async findMany(query: ListQuery) {
  const items = await this.prisma.users.findMany({
    take: query.limit + 1,  // fetch one extra to detect hasMore
    cursor: query.cursor ? { id: decodeCursor(query.cursor) } : undefined,
    skip: query.cursor ? 1 : 0,
    orderBy: { created_at: 'desc' },
    where: { /* filters */ },
  });

  const hasMore = items.length > query.limit;
  if (hasMore) items.pop();

  const nextCursor = hasMore ? encodeCursor(items[items.length - 1].id) : null;
  return { items, pagination: { nextCursor, hasMore, limit: query.limit } };
}
```

### Counts

Büyük tablolarda `count()` yavaş. İhtiyaç varsa:
- Stored aggregates (materialized view)
- Approximate count (`pg_class.reltuples`)
- Pagination'da `hasMore` yeter (total count gereksiz)

## Prisma Schema Conventions

```prisma
// apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma
model users {
  id                         String    @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid
  sicil                      String    @unique @db.VarChar(8)
  first_name                 String    @db.VarChar(100)
  last_name                  String    @db.VarChar(100)
  email                      String    @unique @db.Text  // encrypted deterministic
  phone                      String?   @db.Text           // encrypted probabilistic
  password_hash              String?
  is_active                  Boolean   @default(true)
  created_at                 DateTime  @default(now())
  updated_at                 DateTime  @updatedAt
  // relations
  roles                      user_roles[]
  sessions                   sessions[]
  created_processes          processes[] @relation("ProcessStarter")
  
  @@index([is_active, created_at])
  @@index([company_id, is_active])
}
```

Conventions:
- snake_case (PostgreSQL native)
- UUID PK (`@db.Uuid`)
- `created_at`, `updated_at` standart
- Soft delete: `is_active Boolean @default(true)` — `deleted_at` yerine
- Index explicit — filter combinations için composite index

## Migration Pattern

Yeni migration:

```bash
# Schema düzenle
# apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma — add field

# Migration oluştur (dev DB'ye uygular + migration file)
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name add_user_hire_date
```

Migration file naming: `<timestamp>_<verb>_<noun>`:
- `20260115120000_add_user_phone_column`
- `20260120143000_create_index_users_email`
- `20260201100000_rename_sicil_to_employee_number`

### Migration Review Checklist

Her migration PR'ında:
- [ ] Breaking change mi? Expand-contract pattern uygulanıyor mu?
- [ ] Large table ALTER? `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` kullan
- [ ] DROP var mı? Rollback SQL yaz
- [ ] Backfill gerekiyor mu? Performance impact değerlendir
- [ ] Row-level lock süresi?

### Zero-Downtime Migration (Expand-Contract)

Breaking schema change için 5 adım:

1. **Expand** — new column nullable
2. **Dual write** — code hem eski hem yeni kolona yazar
3. **Backfill** — eski data yeni kolona (batch script)
4. **Switch read** — code yeni kolondan okur
5. **Contract** — eski kolonu drop et (1 hafta sonra)

Her adım ayrı PR + deploy.

### `migrate deploy` vs `db push`

- **`prisma migrate deploy`** — prod + staging. Migration files uygular. Idempotent.
- **`prisma db push`** — dev only. Fast iteration. Migration file YOK.
- **Prod'da `db push` asla çalıştırılmaz.**

## Raw SQL

`$queryRaw` / `$executeRaw` — yalnızca Prisma'nın yetersiz kaldığı durumlarda. Template literal kullan (parameterized):

```typescript
// ✓ Safe
await this.prisma.$queryRaw`
  SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ${email} AND is_active = true
`;

// ✗ YASAK
await this.prisma.$queryRawUnsafe(
  `SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '${email}'`  // SQL injection
);
```

ESLint rule: `$queryRawUnsafe`, `$executeRawUnsafe` banned (kod review'da explicit ADR gerekli).

## Audit Log (Special Table)

`audit_logs` append-only. UPDATE/DELETE PostgreSQL trigger ile engel:

```sql
CREATE TRIGGER trigger_audit_logs_prevent_modification
BEFORE UPDATE OR DELETE ON audit_logs
FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION audit_logs_prevent_modification();
```

Ayrıca DB role:

```sql
REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE ON audit_logs FROM leanmgmt_app;
GRANT SELECT, INSERT ON audit_logs TO leanmgmt_app;
```

Chain hash trigger otomatik compute (INSERT before). Application code hash compute etmez.

## Indexes

Composite index'ler filter + sort combinations için:

```sql
-- Users list filter + sort
CREATE INDEX users_active_created_idx ON users (is_active, created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX users_company_active_idx ON users (company_id, is_active);

-- Processes by starter
CREATE INDEX processes_starter_status_idx ON processes (started_by_user_id, status);

-- Tasks by status
CREATE INDEX tasks_status_sla_idx ON tasks (status, sla_due_at) WHERE status IN ('PENDING', 'CLAIMED');
```

Partial index ile performance gain (yalnız aktif task'lar için).

## Connection Pool

Prisma Client default pool 10. Yüksek load için `DATABASE_URL` query param:

```
postgresql://...?connection_limit=20&pool_timeout=10
```

ECS task başına pool. 3 task × 20 = 60 concurrent connection. Aurora limit kontrol et.

## Banned Patterns

- Controller'da Prisma query (service layer bypass)
- `prisma.$queryRawUnsafe(...)` (SQL injection)
- Transaction yerine sequential `await` (partial write riski)
- `findMany` without pagination (tüm tabloyu belleğe alır)
- Migration reverting via manual SQL (Prisma history bozulur — `migrate reset` dev'de)
- Raw connection management (`prisma.$connect()` boot'ta otomatik)
- N+1 queries (tespit edilirse refactor)
- `skip` offset pagination (cursor kullan)

